A short‑throw dual‑action polisher is an electric polishing tool designed for grinding and polishing automotive paint, metal and other surfaces. It features a shorter polishing track that provides a more refined and controlled polishing effect, making it ideal for detailing complex curved surfaces while reducing swirls and scratches. The market is gaining momentum due to rising demand for automotive detailing services, increased consumer interest in DIY car care, and advancements in motor‑driven polishing technology. Moreover, the growth of e‑commerce channels and expanding aftermarket automotive parts distribution are further accelerating adoption across North America and Asia‑Pacific regions.
